                  "Comments": "Gravel soil. The bulk density of this APSoil reflects weight of fine-earth fraction per volume of bulk soil. Use with gravimetric water contents measured on the fine-earth fraction. Gravel assumed to not hold water as reflected in low SAT, DUL, LL15, LL and AD. The data is a combination of published or supplied measurements, pedotransfer functions, and expert opinion. See Cichota et al. (2013; Soil Research 51: 92-111, http://dx.doi.org/10.1071/SR12338) for a description of the pedotransfer functions. The soil carbon and fresh organic matter settings have been set as those broadly appropriate for permanent productive pastoral systems, see Cichota el al. (2012; Soil Research 50: 694-707, http://dx.doi.org/10.1071/SR12208). Users should take care to adapt these to local conditions before using the data in simulations. FOM values estimated to be 900 kg/ha of FOM in top 600mm of soil and another 100 kg/ha below. Soil C:N ratios taken from soil Loam (Morrinsville NoXXXX).",
